{{about|the scientific journal|the biological process|Cell cycle}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2012}} {{Infobox journal | title = Cell Cycle | cover = | editor = [[Mikhail Blagosklonny|Mikhail V. Blagosklonny]] | discipline = [[Cell biology]] | abbreviation = Cell Cycle | publisher = [[Taylor & Francis]] | country = | frequency = Biweekly | history = 2002-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 3.304 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?journalCode=kccy20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/kccy20/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/kccy20 | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 48778167 | LCCN = 2002212522 | CODEN = CCEYAS | ISSN = 1538-4101 | eISSN = 1551-4005 }} '''''Cell Cycle''''' is a biweekly [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering all aspects of [[cell biology]]. It was established in 2002 with [[Mikhail Blagosklonny|Mikhail V. Blagosklonny]] ([[Roswell Park Cancer Institute]]) as founding [[editor-in-chief]]. Originally published bimonthly, it is now published biweekly.
==Abstracting and indexing== The journal is abstracted and indexed in: {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| *[[Biological Abstracts]]<ref name=BA>{{cite web |url=http://mjl.clarivate.com/cgi-bin/jrnlst/jlresults.cgi?PC=BA |title=Biological Abstracts - Journal List |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2019-06-10}}</ref> *[[BIOSIS Previews]]<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://mjl.clarivate.com/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2019-06-10}}</ref> *[[Chemical Abstracts Service]]<ref name=CASSI>{{cite web |url=http://cassi.cas.org/search.jsp |title=CAS Source Index |publisher=[[American Chemical Society]] |work=[[Chemical Abstracts Service]] |accessdate=2019-06-10}}</ref> *[[Current Contents]]/Life Sciences<ref name=ISI/> *[[Embase]]<ref name=Embase>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/solutions/embase/coverage |title=Embase Coverage |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Embase |accessdate=2019-06-10}}</ref> *[[Index Medicus]]/[[MEDLINE]]/[[PubMed]]<ref name=MEDLINE>{{cite web |url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog/101137841 |title=Cell Cycle |work=NLM Catalog |publisher=[[National Center for Biotechnology Information]] |accessdate=2019-06-10}}</ref> *[[Science Citation Index Expanded]]<ref name=ISI/> *[[Scopus]]<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=https://www.scopus.com/sourceid/18455 |title=Source details: Cell Cycle |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus preview |accessdate=2019-06-10}}</ref> }} According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2017 [[impact factor]] of 3.304.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2018 |chapter=Cell Cycle |title=2017 Journal Citation Reports |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]] |title-link=Journal Citation Reports}}</ref>
